    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pantropical genus containing around 150 species of flowering plants. Together with the African Cola genus (125 species), was part of the former family Sterculiaceae, whose members were noted for having separate male and female flowers borne in often quite large and branched inflorescences. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
